Allright, Zardus left Nemesis in charge when I went camping in the
summer, and when I came back, Nemesis enforcer was being chased out of
the base by weaponfire. Whatever events led up to that, Zardus assumed
that Wolfgang was a traitor, had him slagged, and then put him in a
torture chamber.

::FZ::

FZ shakes his head. Repeating questions over and over was pointless.

"I did what any leader would do, eliminate anyone who is showing signs
of betrayal. Now, I'm sure you don't want to stand here talking about
this, so why don't we proceed to other matters?"

He steps back and motions toward the door.
